HEADWORD: Fetid
<hw>Fet"id</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fetidus</ets>, <ets>foetidus</ets>, fr. <ets>fetere</ets>,
<ets>foetere</ets>, to have an ill smell, to stink: cf. F.
<ets>f⟦eacute⟧tide</ets>.]</ety> <def>Having an offensive smell;
stinking.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Most putrefactions . . . smell either <qex>fetid</qex> or
moldy.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

